cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
1) cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a privacy-preserving construction for auction mechanism design, which involves cryptographic techniques to prevent adversaries from learning unnecessary information. 
2) cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses auction mechanism design, which is a topic closely related to game theory. 
3) cs.DB (Databases) - The paper deals with big data and proposes an auction mechanism design that can handle the velocity, volume, and variety of big data. 
4) cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes an efficient and scalable auction mechanism design that approximates NP-hard problems and avoids the design based on garbled circuits. 
5) cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the veracity of stakeholders in the auction mechanism design, which is related to the trustworthiness of data used in machine learning.
